import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['budgetYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['budgetYear'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['budgetYear'])]
    data['budgetYear'] = data['budgetYear'].dt.year

    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    data.boxplot(column='value', by='budgetYear', ax=ax)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of values across budget years?', wrap=True)
    plt.suptitle('')
    plt.xlabel('Budget Year')
    plt.ylabel('Value')
    plt.legend(title='Budget Years', loc='upper right')

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['forecastYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecastYear'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['forecastYear'])]
    
    plt.plot(data['forecastYear'], data['value'])
    plt.xlabel('Forecast Year')
    plt.ylabel('Value')
    plt.title('What is the trend of values over forecast years?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(['Value'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['budgetYear'], data['value'])

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['forecastYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecastYear'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['forecastYear'])]
    data['forecastYear'] = data['forecastYear'].dt.year

    plt.hist(data['value'], bins=20, alpha=0.75, label='Value', color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Value')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of values across forecast years?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    avg_value_by_budgetYear = data.groupby('budgetYear')['value'].mean()
    ax = avg_value_by_budgetYear.plot(kind='bar', color='blue')
    plt.title('What is the average value for each budget year?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Budget Year')
    plt.ylabel('Average Value')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Average Value'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
